executor_description: This endpoint receives devices variables values
This endpoint lists all of a user’s existing devices by label.
This endpoint reads the last value of a variable.
This endpoint creates values for a variable.
This endpoint deletes a given variable.
This endpoint partially updates a variable, allowing for individual field updates.
This endpoint obtains an existing device variable and its details.
This endpoint updates a variable.
This endpoint lists the values of a variable.

This endpoint creates a new datasource.  A datasource has a number of variables and a context where the properties are stored. For example, a datasource called “Delivery Truck” may have the following properties: {“City”:”Boston”} or {“Type”:”Truck”}.  Properties are not meant to change dynamically over time; they are metadata that help you describe your datasource (device).

This endpoint obtains an existing datasource and its details.  It also returns additional fields not required during the creation of the datasource: number_of_variables: Shows the number of variables contained by the datasource. last_activity: Returns the date of last activity.
This endpoint deletes a given datasource, specified by its ID.
This endpoint updates a datasource, you need to provide all the required fields.
This endpoint lists the variables of a specified datasource, showing all variable fields.
This endpoint lists all the user’s existing datasources.
This endpoint partially updates a datasource, allowing for individual field updates.
This endpoint returns a variable and its details. It shows additional fields than those required during the variable’s creation.
Update Variable
This endpoint lists all variables owned by a user.
This endpoint returns the values of the specified variable.  Every value will be timestamped with a value in milliseconds according to the POSIX standard.
Partially Update Variable
This endpoint deletes a given variable, specified by its ID.
This endpoint allows statistics to be computed over a temporal subset of a variable’s values. The subset is given by the values between [start, end].
This endpoint creates a new value within the specified variable.  Every value has a timestamp that can either be specified manually by the device, or automatically by the server.
This endpoint allows you to delete values between specified start and end times.
This endpoint returns max values resample by mean function for a given list of variable IDs and a specified time frame
Returns the epoch timestamp.
